.TH HELP OLC
.UC
.SH COMMAND 
help \- display information about a command
.SH USAGE
.B help <command>
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
The command 'help' prints out information about OLC commands.  If
you simply type 'help', it prints a brief description of OLC.  If
you  type  'help <command>', it prints a short description of the
specified command.  You can get a  list  of  commands  and  short
descriptions of what they do by typing '?' at the OLC prompt.
